<br>
When Velious came out, people were again sickened by the fact that even lower level characters could get comparable items to the ones they worked so hard for.  And then when ST and Ntov finally started getting explored, people couldn't even believe some of these items that were dropping.  They HAD to be fakes!!<br>
<br>
Now with Luclin out, Verant has once again spread a plague across the earth, sickening people far and wide with items that should not be so easy to get, or possibly not even exist at all.<br>
<br>
Here's the point. . .with each new expansion come new challenges and blah blah blah. . .and with that, VI needs to improve the quality of the players' gear in order for them to remain equipped well enough to explore the new expansion.  So, in essence, an item you worked so hard for a year ago really would be much less useful today as it was back then.  Take Cobalt armor for instance. . .I remember when this armor was just a myth.  Now, this stuff has become twink gear to many people because it can no longer stand up to the improvements VI made to mobs in each expansion.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I've rambled again, as I do sometimes.  I like to get offtrack a lot, so don't mind me or this post, pls.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Just remember that uber items a year ago aren't so uber anymore  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7657" target="_blank">Evisceros Headcutter</a><BR>
